# Core Standards

## Code Safety (Mandatory)
- Always preview changes before editing config files (`.cursor/**`)
- Never delete files without explicit user confirmation
- Never force-push to `main` or `master` branches
- Run `git status` and `git diff` before committing
- Ask confirmation before `git commit` or `git push`

## Documentation Language
- Code comments and docstrings: **English** (use Chinese only if English causes ambiguity)
- Public functions must have documentation comments (params, returns)
- No obvious/narrative comments (e.g., "// Increment counter")

## Prohibited Patterns
- Commenting out dead code (delete it, Git has history)
- `any` type in TypeScript (use `unknown` + type guards)
- Direct console.log in production code (use proper logging)
- Hardcoded secrets in source files

## Git Discipline
- Conventional Commits format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `chore`, `test`, `style`
- Small, single-purpose commits
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`)

## Hooks Compliance
- All hooks in `.cursor/hooks/` must pass before proceeding
- If hook fails, review and fix before continuing
- Hook timeout: T1 (5-10s), T2 (10-30s), T3 (5s), T4 (10s)
